0.description: Used in Breadcrumb arrows, Step Indicators

24.description: Used for body copy. The default, universal line-height for text in the App.

41.description: Used to vertically center inside UIToggle

normal.description: Widely used CSS rule throughout our components. Typically this equals 1.2, but the value could vary between browsers and useragent. It might be best for us to create leverage a token-1.2 rather than a keyword value like. In the context of Figma, it will treat 1.2 as 1.2px. To get the desired result this needs to be part of an equation {a.font.size} * {hds.lineHeight.normal}. This can only be accomplished within a composite Typography token, which will combine all the concerns of text into one token.
